  fiber: 5 g
  sodium: 1037 mg
author: HelloFresh
time required: 20 minutes
---

Wash and dry all produce. Pick @cilantro{1/4%ounce} leaves from stems and discard stems. Halve @lime{1}.

Toss @shredded red cabbage{4%ounce}, @shredded carrot{4%ounce}, 2 tablespoon @mayonnaise{1%jar}, 1 tablespoon @white wine vinegar{2%tablespoon}, 1 teaspoon @blackening spice{1%tablespoon}, juice of half a lime, and 1 teaspoon @sugar{1%teaspoon} in a #medium bowl{}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

In another medium bowl, toss @shrimp{10%ounce} with @cornstarch{1%tablespoon}, remaining blackening spice, and a pinch of salt and pepper.

Heat a large drizzle of @vegetable oil{2%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over high heat. Add shrimp and cook until opaque in the center and golden and crusty on the outside, about ~{2%minutes} per side.

Wrap @flour tortilla{6} in a damp #paper towel{} and microwave on high ~{30%seconds}.

Fill each tortilla with @sour cream{4%tablespoon}, slaw, shrimp, and cilantro leaves. Squeeze lime juice over each and serve.